cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.GR 

The paper presents a novel dataset for tailings dam detection using satellite images, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for classification, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The dataset was built using georeferenced images, which involves Geographic Information Systems (GIS), making cs.GR (Graphics) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the use of the original catalog information for classification, which involves information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves data processing and management, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
